TextBody:
Hello Paul, 

Thank you for connecting Netwrix Technical Support!
We are aligning your ticket with an engineer to assist with your issue. They will reach out to you as soon as possible. 

In the meantime, please clarify: have you run this job after upgrading to 11.6? Could you please download the job log files to the ticket? 

Also, could you execute the following script on the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor console server and provide output to check the current build:

#Netwrix/Stealth, PostgreSQL, Python application versions:
Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Product |
Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "*Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
Sort-Object | Format-Table Name,Version,InstallDate -AutoSize

Thank you!

Best Regards,
Ilia Kudashev
Support Engineer EMEA

TextBody:
Hey Paul,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix technical support. 

Has the Active Directory > 6. Activity > 0.Collection > AD_ActivityCollection job run successfully recently? The most common cause of that error is when NEA is trying to generate a report, but their hasn't been a recent successful data collection.

We can also set up a remote session to review the issue, just use the link below at your convenience to schedule:
